How I Manage Patients with Chronic Myeloid Leukemia (CML): Perspectives from 
Clinical Practice.

Guru Murthy GS(1).

Author information:
(1)Division of Hematology & Oncology, Medical College of Wisconsin, Milwaukee, 
WI, USA.

The management of chronic myeloid leukemia (CML) has remarkably changed in the 
last 20 years with the availability of tyrosine kinase inhibitors (TKI). Most 
patients with chronic phase CML now have a life expectancy like that of age 
matched controls. Understanding the practical aspects of choosing the 
appropriate TKI, monitoring response and side-effects are key to long term 
success. Currently, treatment cessation is also an option in patients achieving 
sustained deep molecular response. Novel agents are needed in patients with lack 
of response to TKI and in those with advanced disease.

